### 1. Register a new user (Staff)
# Create a user with a BCrypt encrypted password
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "username": "johndoe",
    "password": "password123",
    "email": "john.doe@sakila.com",
    "active": true
}

### 2. Login to get JWT
# Save the response token to use in the headers below
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "johndoe",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Customer Service (REST) - GET All
GET http://localhost:8080/customer/all
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Business Service (GraphQL) - Query Stores
# Use a JSON body for the GraphQL query
POST http://localhost:8080/business/graphql
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ allStores { id managerStaffId addressId } }"
}

### 5. Inventory Service (SOAP) - Get Film
# Call the SOAP endpoint with XML payload
POST http://localhost:8080/inventory/ws
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: text/xml

<soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/" xmlns:soap="http://sakila.com/soap">
   <soapenv:Header/>
   <soapenv:Body>
      <soap:getFilmRequest>
         <soap:id>1</soap:id>
      </soap:getFilmRequest>
   </soapenv:Body>
</soapenv:Envelope>

### 6. Reports Service (WebSockets)
# To test WebSockets, use a browser or tool like 'wscat' or a simple JS client:
# URL: ws://localhost:8080/reports-ws?token={{token}}
# Send message: "get-sales"
